# Working on VibeKB (Cursor)

The **canonical, repository-owned** workflow lives in `CLAUDE.md`. This rule is a
pointer so Cursor discovers it automatically — read `CLAUDE.md` for the full
lifecycle. Do not duplicate the workflow here; if they ever disagree, `CLAUDE.md`
wins.

## Do this every session

- **Start with** `php tools/vibekb.php status` for orientation (provenance,
  current work, handoff next-action, drift).
- **VibeKB is self-hosted:** the active `.vibekb/` describes VibeKB itself. Models
  of other apps under `examples/` are demonstrations, **not** the active model.
- **The product is locked:** VibeKB explains *what the software is currently
  doing*, organized around **functionality**. It is not a docs generator, memory
  archive, code browser, or activity log (see `PRODUCT.md`).

## The lifecycle (from `CLAUDE.md`)

orient → record work (`.vibekb/work/current.md`) → implement → find impact
(`php tools/vibekb.php affected --since <base>`) → verify honestly → update the
living model (records, memory, diagrams, provenance) → update the handoff →
`php tools/vibekb.php check` + `php tools/vibekb.php generate`.

## Honesty

Distinguish intended / implemented / verified. Never claim `verified-*` you did
not confirm. Never imply VibeKB auto-updates. Keep the app on PHP 8.2 with no
build step, no database, and no external/AI API; escape all output.

## Before finishing

`php tools/vibekb.php check` clean, `php tools/test-topology.php` OK, `/docs`
regenerated, handoff accurate.
